class=m><span class=title> Feerrott</span><hr size=1> As a dark elf at level 25, I find the higher level lizards in Feerrott to be pretty easy.  Not horribly magic resistant, and typical old world low hps.  Right now I am camped at the pillar-bridge and the 2-spawn on the far side isn't that tough.  Root one, pull the other, if necessary train it to Bouncer Hurd.<br>
<br>
Lizards drop FS and bronze weapons fairly often, and there are friendly vendors in zone and a bank 1 zone away.<br>
<br>
Its also easy to get to:<br>
1) Gate to Cazic Thule (safe as long as you don't leave pyramid)<br>
2) Evac to ZI<br>
3) Zone out to Feerrott<br>
4) Levitate self<br>
5) Invis self<br>
6) Run to Oggok and bind<br>
<br>
Getting sow and/or clarity is a big help here obviously too, but not really required.  Just keep Leatherskin up for those times that root breaks and remember that discretion is the better part of valor. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Araxin, young wizard of Saryrn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uezobey12.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ezobey12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 5:47:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Twilight Sea?</span><hr size=1> I have heard that the zone in Luclin, Twilight Sea might be something to check out for leveling from 25 to 40ish.<br>
<br>
Lots of mobs there, and you have a city zone right next to it to bind in and buy/sell/bank your loot.<br>
<br>
There are tons of elementals you can single pull and kite or root nuke.  Just make sure you have sow and gate memed if you need it.  There is also a bunch of NPC quests here, not sure if any are good or not.<br>
<br>
Good Luck. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukekenewah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kekenewah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 5:53:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mars Seru</span><hr size=1> Go kill mobs in Mars seru, like greyhoppers and stonegrabbers.  You can group at the rock.  If you solo you can Root/nuke to 29, then kite stuff once you get bonds of force. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelasto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 6:04:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mars Seru</span><hr size=1> Can solo or group in loio if you so wish. There is a reason why it is so popular .. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufelricuberfizzle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felric Uberfizzle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 8:24:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> From 26 to 29 perma camp yourself at the evil eyes in Beholder - SOLO. Start with 1 spawn,then move to both spawns at 27-28 range. (depending on your mana pool)<br>
<br>
6 minute static spawn. 3-8 plat per kill in cash and cash items. Occasionally they drop a PBB that sells for about 100-150p in the Bazaar. There's a merchant just outside the zone in EK.<br>
<br>
If you bring a partner, the eye's can charm them to kill you.<br>
<br>
Enjoy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> edit:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Added thoughts.....<br>
<br>
At each spawn there is a rock that is near it on the wall. you can safely sit on the rock to med without attracting the minos. They stop agroing around 28.<br>
<br>
As for taking out the eye:<br>
<br>
First kill attempt the eye will have a pet up. Blast the eye, root the pet if needed, but finish off the eye. After that, just blast before it can spawn a pet. No rooting or kiting. Just Nuke.<br>
<br>
 <p><p style="font-size:12px"><b><span style="color:009900">Felric Uberfizzle</span><br></b>
	Mighty Tykes Channeler of the 52nd Season<br>
	Brell Serilis<br>
	<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162145">Profile...</a></b></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufelricuberfizzle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felric Uberfizzle</A> at: 8/27/02 8:30:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushealie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shealie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 8:41:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> If you don't mind the Dismal Rage and Opal Darkbriar faction hits, look up my rogue friend Osargen in Highkeep. His loot is nonexistent, but he's on the 6 minute timer and should get you about a blue per kill at your level. Sit diagonal to his spawn point in the jail cell and you can mostly avoid the green (but annoying) prisoners near him. You'll need to root him but that alteration skill has to raise somehow, right?<br>
<br>
I'm told that if your mana's good you can run back and forth between him and Lislia Goldtune upstairs. Haven't tried it, though -- I save Osargen for when I'm doing a couple of things at once. <p>Shealie
Wizard of the 29th Non-Critical Blast
Mithaniel Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoxoxoxoxox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oxoxo Xoxox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 8:50:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.swmed.edu/libraryis/eq/wizsig4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> Get buffs in Bazaar/nexus and solo or grp in Marus Seru <p>Mistress <b><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68788'>Oxoxo Xoxox</a></b> Sorcerer<BR><b><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235386'>Yumkin Stumpyshorts</a></b> Cleric<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.mithrilweb.com" target="blank"><img src="http://www.queensidecastle.com/eq/Sorcerersig3.jpg" border="0"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usaundradwarfstomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saundra Dwarfstomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 8:50:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> Nope, gotta be mamas in Everfrost...  quadding or not, tusks sell for +/- ten pp a piece   =)<br>
Its got to be the best area to learn to quad... theres room to run, no other high level mobs (except IGs and they dont wander, and Martar), you can run to guards (or zone to perma if you are not loved by guards here).<br>
<br>
You can usually catch 2 or 3 mamas at the end of the island in the middle of the frozen river (N end).  <br>
AE snare, trot S down the river a bit...<br>
AE nuke, trot some more...<br>
rinse, repeat!<br>
<br>
(Doh! Work logged me in as my old DAOC char. please pretend that reads Shelbylynn Talhammer  &lt;sigh&gt;) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usaundradwarfstomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saundra Dwarfstomper</A> at: 8/27/02 8:54:26 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utathagatavalar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TathagataValar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 5:26:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> Thank you all very much for your help.<br>
Im not worried about cash, im right there and would prefer higher than blue mobs. That said Ive tried Marus Seru and found it no good, the mobs there have HUGE hitpoints and regen and an alarming rate. LOIO doesnt have any exp compared to the Luclin zones anymore.<br>
<br>
I will try Twilight Sea and Dawnshroud tonight and see how they go. HHK sounds good too.<br>
Thanks for all the info. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugardack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gardack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 7:38:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> Try SK at the big Aviak tower. I did that area the past 2 nights with my gf playing her level 46 druid pulling for me. On Avocets and Harriers she'd snare and fire debuff. On rooks and darters she'd just snare. Root and mana free arm dot to finish the mobs once they're at 45% so I have plenty of mana for the next mob she pulled.<br>
<br>
Went from 24-26 in 2 nights there, around 2 hours tops each night. Plan to stay here till at least 29, then try some quads once I get the AE snare and if I ever find the runes I need for the level 24 Column AE. <p>Baron 
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31117>Gardack Snowdevil</a>
<BR>
Baron 
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=161978>Ivain Frostfury</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utathagatavalar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TathagataValar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 9:24:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 25-30 camp</span><hr size=1> Gardack. You could have made 24 to 26 in an hour with your druids help in Paludal. <br>
That, I think is my problem. At 25 I am making 4/5ths of a blue per dark blue kill in Paludal (they are only just dark blue). But at 26 the exp will run dry here and Im afraid that after the awesome exp of this zone Im jsut going to be disappointed everywhere else I go. To give you some indication of what I have found so far:<br>
Paludal - Easy kills, dk blue = 4/5ths exp, lt blue = 1/5th exp<br>
SolA - dk blue = 4/5th exp, no lt blue, extremely tough zone (cant single pull and wizards are dangerous).<br>
SK - yellow (spire gnolls) = 1/2 blue, dk blue (rooks) = 1/5th blue.<br>
LOIO - Dk blue (gobs in tunnels) = 1/2 blue<br>
Merus Seru - Dk blue = 1/2 blue, extremely tough mob, huge HP and regen<br>
Echo Caverns - Dk blue (needelites) = 1 blue per kill, zone is always camped.<br>
<br>
Thats what Ive tried so far, obviously Echo is the best so far but the problem is a limited spawn and contested camp. If this interests anyone Im happy to keep you informed of other zones I try. Just remember that I am not soloing but have the help of a 45 Druid, so these zones may not be good for the average level 25 or so Wizard. Also, cash and facilities do not come into account here, just speed of experience. Therefore downtime, evacs, having to zone, etc count more for me than anything else.<br>
Its not so much the exp per kill, if I can pull 4 mob that are very weak but offer 1/4 blue each im better off than pulling one mob that hits hard with huge HPs but offers 3/4 exp.<br>
<br>
Im still very interested in all the replies and Im sure those that dont help me will help others, so keep them coming.<br>
<br>
Thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=19994.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=19994.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19994.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=19994.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=19994.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19994.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19994.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizar